{"id":38124,"date":"2022-08-15T11:02:13","date_gmt":"2022-08-15T07:02:13","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=38124"},"modified":"2022-08-15T15:06:06","modified_gmt":"2022-08-15T11:06:06","slug":"maruf-joy-to-sinners","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/08\/15\/maruf-joy-to-sinners\/","title":{"rendered":"Ma\u2019ruf on Mercy: O Allah, bring joy to the sinners who repent"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibrahim ibn al-Utrush reported: Ma\u2019ruf al-Karkhi, may Allah have mercy on him, was upon the Tigris river and we were with him as we passed by some people in a boat misbehaving, singing and beating the drum. We said to Ma\u2019ruf, \u201cO Abu Mahfuz, do you not see these people on the water disobeying Allah Almighty? Pray to Allah against them!\u201d Ma\u2019ruf raised his hands to the sky and he said, \u201cO Allah, my God, my Master! O Allah, I ask You to bring them joy in the Hereafter as You have brought them joy in the world!\u201d One of his companions said, \u201cWe asked you to pray against them! We did not ask you to pray for them!\u201d Ma\u2019ruf said, \u201cIf Allah brings them joy in the Hereafter, then He has accepted their repentance. It will not harm you at all.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n 9\/70<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0625\u0628\u0631\u0627\u0647\u064a\u0645 \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0637\u0631\u0648\u0634 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0643\u0627\u0646 \u0645\u0639\u0631\u0648\u0641 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0631\u062e\u064a \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u062c\u0644\u0629 \u0648\u0646\u062d\u0646 \u0645\u0639\u0647 \u0625\u0630 \u0645\u0631 \u0628\u0646\u0627 \u0623\u0642\u0648\u0627\u0645 \u0623\u062d\u062f\u0627\u062b \u0641\u064a \u0632\u0648\u0631\u0642 \u064a\u063a\u0646\u0648\u0646 \u0648\u064a\u0636\u0631\u0628\u0648\u0646 \u0628\u0627\u0644\u0